data.Name: Carbon Leaf
data.Bio: Some bands insist on dragging listeners into their world, but Richmond, VA's Carbon Leaf works towards a more admirable and considerably more difficult goal – that of letting perfect strangers feel that the band understands their world. Since 1992, the band has succeeded in doing just that -- and on its third Vanguard release, Nothing Rhymes With Woman, has created a soundtrack suitable for multiple worlds. “For me, this is an album that’s focused on growth and maturity, but it’s not deadly serious,” says front man Barry Privett.
